data.chText: （通常表示愤怒、决心或不安时）捏紧，攥紧（拳头等），咬紧（牙齿等）
data.enText: when you clench your hands, teeth, etc., or when they clench , you press or squeeze them together tightly, usually showing that you are angry, determined or upset
He clenched his fists in anger.
Through clenched teeth she told him to leave.

data.chText: 他的拳头慢慢地捏紧，直捏得指关节都发白了。
data.enText: His fists clenched slowly until his knuckles were white.
to hold sth tightly and firmly
Her pen was clenched between her teeth.

word_means: 钉牢；咬紧牙关；咬牙切齿；敲弯的钉头

means: (通常表示愤怒、决心或不安时)捏紧，攥紧(拳头等)，咬紧(牙齿等)
钉牢；咬紧牙关；咬牙切齿；敲弯的钉头

example: he released his clasp on my arm
he has a strong grip for an old man
she kept a firm hold on the railing

tr: a small slip noose made with seizing

value.def: When you clench your fist or your fist clenches, you curl your fingers up tightly, usually because you are very angry.

example.ex: Alex clenched her fists and gritted her teeth...
example.tran: 亚历克丝攥紧拳头，牙咬得咯咯响。

example.ex: She pulled at his sleeve and he turned on her, fists clenching again before he saw who it was.
example.tran: 她拉了拉他的袖子，他双拳再次握紧，气冲冲地转过身来，这才发现是她。
双拳紧握的愤怒的抗议者们

value.def: When you clench your teeth or they clench, you squeeze your teeth together firmly, usually because you are angry or upset.

example.ex: Patsy had to clench her jaw to suppress her anger...
example.tran: 帕奇只得咬紧牙关压住怒气。

example.ex: Slowly, he released his breath through clenched teeth.
example.tran: 他从紧咬的牙缝间慢慢地舒了口气。

value.tran: (通常指生气、不安时)咬紧(牙齿)，咬牙切齿

value.def: If you clench something in your hand or in your teeth, you hold it tightly with your hand or your teeth.

example.ex: I clenched the arms of my chair.
